Installation Steps:

Step1: Unzip the file red5recorder.zip and you will get "red5recorder" directory.

Step2: Upload the "red5recorder" directory into your webapps directory of your red5 installation. Dont change the directory name and keep it "red5recorder".

Step3: Open the file js/recorder.js. Change the flash variables like "server", "filename" with the suitable file names and exact server location.

Step4: Open the index.html file into your browser and start recording.

Step5: After finish click on stop. automatically you will get one .flv file generated under the directory "Streams". The file name by default "recorded_audio.flv". You can change it from the recorder.js.
